website_summaries.verdict: With many satisfied felines, owners also love this wet food's nutritious ingredients, grain-free formula, and variety.
pros: Most cats can't get enough of the tasty flavors that includes chicken and shrimp, ocean fish, and tuna
Doesn't cause stomach issues for most sensitive cats
cons: Rare reports of cats that didn't like it, but it appeals to most finicky eaters

customer_reviews.title: Beware of bones
customer_reviews.text: Cats loved it however found fish bones in food after my cat began choking while eating this. Scared me to death. I searched other containers from two different cases and sure enough more bones. I rather give them Fancy feast might not be as healthy but I have never once found a bone in their products. If you do use this brand then always check before feeding it to them! i do use the dry food and haven’t found any issues and my cats love that too. But I can’t and won’t put them at risk by purchasing this wet food product ever again!
customer_reviews.author: Real Customer

customer_reviews.title: Like everyone else
customer_reviews.text: Like everyone else... I found bones!!! How could a company sell a product that clearly has bones in it and amazon allows them to sell it. Hopefully my cat is okay. I feel extremely angry!!!
customer_reviews.author: Danielle Gibson

customer_reviews.title: Allergic Reaction
customer_reviews.text: My poor cat scratched himself bald after eating this food. According to our vet, lots of cats are allergic to something in Rachel Ray's Nutrish. Not so natural after all I guess.
customer_reviews.author: jtwash

customer_reviews.title: The expiration date: look before you buy!
customer_reviews.text: When i received these and fed it to my cats, they loved it. So I just reordered another 36 cans. Then i noticed the expiration date was July, 2015. My cats are going to be pissed, but when that next shipment hits my door.......back it goes even b/4 opening it. Selling expired food is not cool and quality control is missing here or just a lack of caring. I am truly upset about this.
customer_reviews.author: hendrisd

customer_reviews.title: made my cat sick
customer_reviews.text: My cat seemed to like it just fine, but then she got extremely sick and threw up 4 times in one day and had terrible diarrhea. She had never thrown up before so it was extremely worrisome. I've gotten the dry food from Rachael Ray and it seemed to be fine. I'm not sure if we got a bad batch or what, but I won't be buying it again, I don't want to put my poor little one through that again.
customer_reviews.author: Nebula

customer_reviews.title: Enjoy the vet bills.
customer_reviews.text: Cats loved it for about 2 weeks then vomiting and litter box issues like crazy. Took them both to the vet he suggested to take them off the food and sure enough everything was fine again. I horrified to think what was in there. I ordered a few cases at a time when they were on sale so I have plenty to spare and may be taking legal action. Avoid this product!
customer_reviews.author: DannyD

customer_reviews.title: Concerned regarding fish bones in product
customer_reviews.text: Our two cats enjoy this food but I have found pieces of fish bone in the product as others have mentioned. After a scare I’m no longer going to utilize this product. I feel badly not supporting this but am too concerned about the well being of our much loved pets.
customer_reviews.author: RTG

customer_reviews.title: Very good
customer_reviews.text: First of all, why leave a one-star review if your cat just doesn't like the food? That doesn't mean it's a bad product. I like this cat food because it has pieces of meat in it rather than being a homogenous paste. It also helps that it's grain-free because I need to watch my cat's weight closely. She loves the taste which doesn't mean much as she eats basically anything, but so far it's been very good for managing her weight. As always, the recommended feeding amount is probably too high, my cat gets one tub per day along with a couple of spoons of kibble.
customer_reviews.author: JM

customer_reviews.title: BONES 😡 BONES 😡 BONES 😡
customer_reviews.text: How in the world are you selling food saturated in BONES?! You’re aware cats can easily choke on bones this size, correct? After I found the first bone I opened up 3 more containers and I will tell you 3 out of 4 containers has multiple bones in them. SHUT IT DOWN RACHAEL RAY. You’re going to have a lawsuit on your hands.
customer_reviews.author: Josh

customer_reviews.title: Great Product!!!!
customer_reviews.text: This is the only flavor of Rachael Ray Nutrish wet cat food my cat will eat. Chicken only! He is a 30 yr old Maine Coon & he will be 31 yrs old July 16, 2018, 'Jimmy'. The stores don't stock enough of the Chicken Purrcata....he deserves to be fussy at his age. Thanks Amazon! >^.^<~yeps (Got some more for my cat today...you made him happy! Thanks.)
customer_reviews.author: Marcie

customer_reviews.title: This stuff looks and smells like the stuff you can get at the dollar store
customer_reviews.text: Would give it 0 stars if i could. This stuff looks and smells like the stuff you can get at the dollar store. My cat didn't eat it. I tried giving it to the homeless street kitties and they didn't even eat it all. Every time I left a container out they would only eat half of it before walking away. I gave up. Didn't want to torture them with this stuff. Waste of money, had to throw it out. Btw, those street kitties eat the stuff from the dollar store just fine when I'm in a pinch.
customer_reviews.author: Manajuma

customer_reviews.title: I wasn't sure about this...
customer_reviews.text: My cats loved this soft food. I usually give them a bowl of dry food and a small portion of soft (to make sure they get some hydration). I was afraid this may be too rich for the sensitive tummies they sometimes seem to have, but it doesn't seem to be a problem. They both love it and it shows in how soft their fur is now.
customer_reviews.author: KK

customer_reviews.title: Didn't live up to the hype
customer_reviews.text: A few weeks ago I accompanied a friend of mine to the vet, where they gave his dog Rachael Ray Nutrish wet food. He ate that thing up in about two seconds! Naturally, I got on Amazon and bought a sampler pack of Rachael Ray Nutrish Natural Wet Cat Food. Unfortunately the cats weren't very impressed with it - They actually prefer the diet cat food I recently got them. Maybe the dog food is just better quality? Or maybe dogs aren't as picky. Either way, it wasn't worth the money. I'll stick with Purina One.
customer_reviews.author: meredith

customer_reviews.title: WARNING : May cause you to disown your cat...
customer_reviews.text: Looked and smelled just like canned chicken that you would buy for your own supper. Our cats loved it. All that said, it gave our cats the worst smelling gas and frighteningly horrid poops. Paint peeling, eye watering, do we need to call HAZMAT? toxic poops. We started mixing half dry food with half of the Nutrish cup and this seemed to balance everything out. I would not recommend giving this food to your cat at full strength by any means, not unless you have a gas mask and a crisis hotline number handy.
customer_reviews.author: Chelle P.

customer_reviews.title: Made my poor cat sick, don't buy!
customer_reviews.text: I should have read the reviews before buying this cat food. My poor cat, who is 16 years old got horrible diarrhea! First of all, she would only lick the juice. I even cut the pieces smaller thinking it would help, but no. Then the next day she was so sick to her stomach. I could hear her little tummy gurgling. Then came the diarrhea. And the smell, like others said, was aweful! Don't know if Amazon will let me return it or not. I would give it to a rescue organization but I don't want to make those furbabies sick either, so in the trash it will go!!!
customer_reviews.author: K. Jacklin

customer_reviews.title: My cats love them !
customer_reviews.text: Definitely a "better" quality ingredient cat food then most of the worthless chemical and by-product based canned cat food on the market. I use these to supplement my dry food for 3 of my 18.5 year old Bengal cats. They love all the flavors. Never a miss, purchased multiple times over the past year, never disappointed! Of course, not all cats like all food. Buy one at the store, test it out......these are really good ! Big chunks of real fish, chicken, beef, shrimp......not fake molded to look like.......real actual ingredients!
customer_reviews.author: lance bingham

customer_reviews.title: Wtf
customer_reviews.text: My cat isn’t picky. He will eat anything. Loves Rachel Ray dry food. I thought I would try the wet food. I opened it up and it looked like human food, like human chicken and corn. It smelled almost like human food as well. I was sure my cat would love it....He ate half of it then tried to bury it like a cat would bury his poo in a litter box. I left it alone. I came back to it a couple hours later and found that my cat pooped in it. So...I guess that it’s a no for him.
customer_reviews.author: Pank Brown

customer_reviews.title: 😻Nutrish is delish! Gizmo Approved!😻
customer_reviews.text: My lil furball is very picky about wet food. I have tried giving him the healthy cat foods like Instinct, Castor & Pollux, & Organix,, but he would not eat them. Unfortunately, he prefers unhealthy cat foods like friskies, 9 lives, etc. Then Nutrish came out and I saw it was grain free and healthier ingredients. So, I thought I’d give it to Gizmo to try & just like Mikey...he likes it! PS I have not found any bones in my cats food. Maybe they fixed the recipe!
customer_reviews.author: ZombeeUnicorn🦄

customer_reviews.title: Shredding put off my cat
customer_reviews.text: I was so excited to find a really nutritious, natural wet food. But my cat would not eat it. She nibbled a bite or two and then gave up. I suspect it is less about taste and more about the shredded texture. She couldn't seem to get used to the shredding. And her wet food is a supplement to the dry, and after the 2nd day, the nonpreservative wet food smelled strong, even though refrigerated, and at that stage she wouldn't even eat one bite. She smelled it and walked away. So although I wanted to use this more healthful natural product, I ended up giving it to another family for their cat.
customer_reviews.author: marjorie

customer_reviews.title: I wish I would have read ALL the reviews before ...
customer_reviews.text: I wish I would have read ALL the reviews before I bought this for my 10 mos. old Annie. I fed her the first serving before I left for work and when I got home, she had puked all of it up on the kitchen floor. She has never vomited before! I tried a different flavor in the box and she refused to eat them, period! I guess even a chef cannot make a cat food that is safe for them to eat! Won't even donate this to the shelter.
customer_reviews.author: LakotaDLynn

customer_reviews.title: Caution: Fish bones!
customer_reviews.text: My cat loves Nutrish wet food. He always licks it clean. It's grain free and the ingredients seem to be high quality. Be careful with the mackerel and sardine flavor, though. It comes with a lot of fish bones. I often see/hear my cat struggling to pick the bones out. I've some bones that he picked out that were just crazy long and sharp. I'm worried about him swallowing them. I will continue to buy Nutrish but will be avoiding the fish flavors.
customer_reviews.author: AJ

customer_reviews.title: They just love, love
customer_reviews.text: Interesting to switch it up as my cats usually eat the chicken day after day. They just love, love, love this brand. The texture and smell was OK for me. It does matter as I am the one who has to dole it out and I would rather not gag on the smell of cat food first thing in the AM! Easy to clean cups and away into the recycle bin they go. Good price point.
customer_reviews.author: Jan

customer_reviews.title: Subscribe and save. Prime deliver. BUY GOOD FOOD FOR YOUR KIDS.
customer_reviews.text: My Tonkin twins love the meats. So I meats my boyz with some tasty chicken yum yum. NO complaints. If you clean up after your cats when they're done eating, then small pieces of dried chicken which may resemble bones when dried, are not an issue. The complaints i read must have been in regard to the tuna/seafood. Do the math/division. Think about your cat and the trash on the shelf at the dollar store. Think about the no hassle prime that ships at cheaper cost on a subscription. Your cats aren't going anywhere. So subscribe now and save. This food looks and smells like chicken sunday dinner.
customer_reviews.author: Informed Consumer

customer_reviews.title: Just OK
customer_reviews.text: At first my cat loved this cat food, gobbled it down, except for the little squares of something in it. But as about half the box of 12 cups of food had been eaten, Millie would not touch the remaining ones. I had put out one flavor which she refused, then several hours later, I tried another flavor. She went hungry rather than eat them. Something in them that does not agree with her, I will assume. Back to Fancy Feast pate beef flavors which she loves.
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: Designed to look like real meat.....
customer_reviews.text: When my cats lick off all the gravy, it's easy to see that this is NOT real shredded chicken or chunks of fish. It is clearly some super processed formed "meat" (which may in fact have chicken or tuna ingredients, but is DESIGNED to look like the original form of the meat--unless you look closely!) The cats leave that crap behind. Don't be fooled by the nice clear packaging and gravy like I was.
customer_reviews.author: Rochelle Siegel

customer_reviews.title: They seem to love the real fish in these packs and go nuts ...
customer_reviews.text: Our cats have been eating this stuff for about a year. They seem to love the real fish in these packs and go nuts when they eat it. The product is minimally processes and has actual fish meat and chunks in it. Product is made in Thailand which I would normally be a little suspect about but we haven't had any issues with it. I have also read reviews on here talking about fish bones in the containers but have only seen a couple small ones once.
customer_reviews.author: Jimmy

customer_reviews.title: More and more fillers added
customer_reviews.text: At first my cat loved this food, and I've been giving it to him for about 9 months. He'd leave behind these little pate cubes that I can only describe as fillers. At first, there were only like five left in the bowl, so it wasn't very wasteful. As time has gone by, however, there have been more and more of these little filler cubes added, and now he leaves behind most of the food trying to eat around them. There are like 30 of them in one bowl. I've tried to squish them down, but he still eats around them. It's a waste.
customer_reviews.author: JustAGirl83

customer_reviews.title: Ugh
customer_reviews.text: Update: after reading other reviews outside of Amazon I see that this food is not as great as it is made out to be. "Fresh" fish from Thailand! And like others I found a bone in the food and it's got quite a bit of salt in it. While my cat loves this stuff, at the age of 15, I'm not risking bones, high salt content and god knows what other crap is in here. Have already ordered different food. I better do better research next time. Original review: I have never seen my cat devour food so quickly. I like that it is grain free, and appears to have healthy ingredients.
customer_reviews.author: Kelly

customer_reviews.title: Go to catinfo.org! See why dry food is bad!
customer_reviews.text: People please go to catinfo.org and see how bad dry food is for your cat!! And see how some of the highly priced cat foods are very low in protein and high in carbs (even when it says grain free). Read how and why by products got such a bad name and how cats are suffering bc of our stupid mistakes!!! We dont need to buy these fancy named cat foods. We need to read ingredient labels. Look at the composition chart and find the best ones. From there look at ingredients. Check the first 5 or 6 on the list. Even if it has by product it is still better than blue wilderness, rachel ray, and so many others!!!
customer_reviews.author: holly1234

customer_reviews.title: Strong smell and my cat refuses to eat this food.
customer_reviews.text: The portion size was a bit smaller than the cans that I usually buy for our cat, however this was fine as we were looking for a healthier option and portion control anyway. When, I opened the first container of the food the smell was quite powerful and it filled the entire room. My cat ate the first serving, however he would not eat several attempts afterwards. My cat is a little picky but not typically to the point where he will flat out refuse wet food. Maybe he just does not enjoy this flavor, regardless i am stuck with a case and a 1/2 of this food.
customer_reviews.author: Christopher T. White

customer_reviews.title: cats won't finish a serving
customer_reviews.text: I was looking for something to tempt my elderly cats and this was recommended at the pet supply store. I divide the cup of food onto two plates, then give it to the two cats that really need to eat more. They eat maybe 3/4 of what I give them then walk away. Cat #3 then sniffs at the remaining food and "buries" it. For comparison, I also tried Sheba cat food - they scarfed Sheba down followed by an extended face-washing. Portions sizes of Rachael Ray are larger than Sheba (plus the cups are easier to open for me), but I will have to go with the kind that the kitties will eat.
customer_reviews.author: Audrey

customer_reviews.title: Made my cats sick
customer_reviews.text: My cats stopped eating this entirety. They would lick the gravy and that is it. Made a couple of them throw up.
customer_reviews.author: wedjatone

customer_reviews.title: My cat basically said not in her lifetime. She ...
customer_reviews.text: My cat basically said not in her lifetime. She wouldn't even taste it. She evn gave me the WTF is this face and stalked away.
customer_reviews.author: Angel S

customer_reviews.title: Picky eaters ate it!
customer_reviews.text: My cats loved it enough to eat most of it, and they are the kind that likes to just lick wet food dry and leave the "meat", haha. They both ate almost all of a portion - each! However, I bought the chicken in hopes the smell wouldn't knock me down.. but oddly enough the only one with 'fish' in it smelled the best! They're all really strong, but definitely not as bad as most wet food. The ingredients are way better than most, so I don't feel bad giving them a smelly treat now and again, though. Will buy again!
customer_reviews.author: Fyonna Ashley

customer_reviews.title: My cat will not eat these
customer_reviews.text: My cat is the epitome of a picky eater, she only seems to like fish flavors. She will not eat pâtés at all, but she doesn’t want larger chunks in wet food either, she will lick all the moisture out of these foods but not eat the sheds or chunks of meat in food and this food is heavy on. The consistency is that jarred toddler food and has an people friendly presentation. I have gone through dozens of moist foods and she frequently changes her mind about her likes and dislikes. This is the only brand that she totally refuses to eat any flavor of.
customer_reviews.author: SherryQ

customer_reviews.title: Contains Xanthan Gum
customer_reviews.text: I wrote this review on the company's website and it was removed. I dislike when companies can't take an honest review. I gave this to my cats twice a day and was noticing alot of diarrhea. Come to find out it contains Xanthan Gum which is a laxative. I stopped feeding them food with Xanthan Gum and it went away. I posted on the site in hopes they would stop using Gum in there food but they choice to ignore me. If your cats are having problems I would suggest another food.
customer_reviews.author: April Biederman

customer_reviews.title: Nutrish is Great for my Kitty
customer_reviews.text: My picky kittty had reached a stage where she would not eat anything we put out so she started catching rats and mice and birds to eat. Nutrish stopped that as she immediately began eating it. The only problem seems to be that some of the meats are just too large for her mouth. If I chop them she eats all of it. If I don't chop it she leaves the larger pieces. No waste tho because the dogs love the leftovers.
customer_reviews.author: Librarian

customer_reviews.title: Single serve plastic container that is NOT recyclable!
customer_reviews.text: My dog and cat both absolutely love this food but I cannot justify using single serve plastic containers 4 times a day! I'm surprised Rachel Ray doesn't use earth friendly materials. The plastic containers are not made from recycled material and do not have the recycle symbol on them so they cannot be recycled. Sadly, I have to move on. I would love to feed this food to my pets but can't do it at the cost of more plastic in our landfills and oceans. Please find an earth friendly company. Cans are far better than all of this plastic!
customer_reviews.author: Christine

customer_reviews.title: My cat had diarrhea after eating this wet food
customer_reviews.text: The main concern about this product is that my cat felt bad after eating it even though I gave him half of the cup a day (and kibble as other meals). I also tried to give 1/3 but the diarrhea continued. The product seems to contain a lot of oil (it is seen on top of the product). From the ingredient list I can see that it is vegetable oil so I don't see why it is necessary in cat wet food. The food also contains a lot of water. I am not buying this product again and I have no idea what to do with the rest of the cups.
customer_reviews.author: Owl_

customer_reviews.title: My cat would not eat any of these.
customer_reviews.text: My cat would not eat any of the varieties in this product. I tried all 3 and he just turned up his nose. He never refuses food but he did not like this product.
customer_reviews.author: Xaja Mykil

customer_reviews.title: My kitty threw up!
customer_reviews.text: My cat enjoyed the taste, however I have a few complaints. The portion size is way too small. I have a big kitten and he’s growing fast. He would need 3 of these a day in order to meet his normal meal size. Another complaint is that it did not agree with his tummy at all! He never throws up or feels ill and he eats everything!! I found throw up in his room this morning and the only think different that I changed was giving him this food last night. Won’t be doing that again.
customer_reviews.author: April Figueroa

customer_reviews.title: Cat refuses to eat the mysterious filler
customer_reviews.text: After trying a dozen portions and seeing the same uneaten parts (mysterious brown processed cubes), I gave up on this food. I wrote to the company (Smuckers) asking what those cubes were made of and they refused to answer. Really. Three back and forth emails and they flatly refused to divulge what's in that filler nor expressed interest that the cat makes the effort to eat around them. They told me to mush and thoroughly mix them in. lol. If my normally ravenous cat has made it clear those cubes are inedible, I'm not going to try to fool him, thank you very much Smuckers. Until I learn differently, I'm going to assume it's sawdust.
customer_reviews.author: F. Grossman

customer_reviews.title: My 3 cats love it
customer_reviews.text: I usually split 1 container between 3 cats as a daily treat in addition to their basic dry food. I've tried many different brands but they like this one the best. They never leave any leftovers of the Rachel Ray brand but are picky about some of the ingredients in other brands and consistently leave portions uneaten. So considering what is wasted with the others, the slightly higher cost of Rachel Ray is probably not much, if any.
customer_reviews.author: Sandy

customer_reviews.title: My Little Sunshine loves this food!
customer_reviews.text: My cat "Sunshine" had been spitting up her regular food and I noticed she was missing some teeth and probably could not chew her food so I got her the "Rachael Ray Nutrish Chicken Purrcata" Sunshine loved the food from the beginning and has stopped spitting up. I give her half of the cup in the morning and the other half in the evening I have been having problems finding this food local Walmart and Kroger has stopped carrying this food so I have to order it online
customer_reviews.author: M. Stephens

customer_reviews.title: New kitten loves these
customer_reviews.text: I got a new kitten who will not eat anything unless I mix it with KMR milk. I have tried a ton of different cans with no luck. She won't touch dry food or treats so I was getting very worried until I tried these. She loves them and cleans the plate! She is 14 weeks so it's not like she is still weaning. I have never had a kitten that was this picky... sure glad I found something she would eat. (yes I know she's spoiled... duh!)
customer_reviews.author: InUnison

customer_reviews.title: It keeps feeding time 'quiet'
customer_reviews.text: I absolutely LOVE this food. Not only is it a healthy choice, but it's QUIET to feed. I have one cat who likes to eat during the night and we all know what happens when we pop the top of a can of cat food. I can SLOWLY peel back the top label and spoon the food into a small bowl for my Gizzy and the other cats are none the wiser. If I pop a regular can of food I have to deal with ALL the cats wanting to eat. I catch it on sale a lot on Amazon and delivery is fast.
customer_reviews.author: furbysmama

customer_reviews.title: Nope
customer_reviews.text: Portion size is great. My cat loves the taste. But...this stuff has so much salt in it, and I found a couple small bones in them. The fish is shipped from elsewhere so it's not from the U.S. It's to bad that a famous brand like this has so many negative things about it, and it's a shame because my cat really liked the flavor and texture of these. But not worth the high salt content and my cat possibly choking on a bone.
customer_reviews.author: Kelly

customer_reviews.title: My Cats Love them!
customer_reviews.text: Definitely a "better" quality ingredient cat food then most of the worthless chemical and by-product based canned cat food on the market. I use these to supplement my dry food for 3 of my 18.5 year old Bengal cats. They love all the flavors. Never a miss, purchased multiple times over the past year, never disappointed! Of course, not all cats like all food. Buy one at the store, test it out......these are really good ! Big chunks of real fish, chicken, beef, shrimp......not fake molded to look like.......real actual ingredients!
customer_reviews.author: lance bingham

customer_reviews.title: cats love it, but...
customer_reviews.text: Well, my two cats love this food, but they get constipated if I feed it to them on a daily basis. I even tried adding canned pumpkin (which they also seemed to love) but it didn't help. Also, I wish the little cups that the food comes in were bigger. Seems like a waste of packaging with so many little cups. I was hoping this cat food would replace the Trader Joe's Tuna For Cats that was discontinued, but due to the constipation, I can only feed it to them occasionally.
customer_reviews.author: Jennifer B.

customer_reviews.title: Awful for your kitty
customer_reviews.text: My cat kept throwing up every time he ate it.. at first I thought it's just hair balls or he ate too fast, but no - he reacted like this to every single can (5 total) only of this brand. He doesn't react like this to any other brands I threw away the rest.
customer_reviews.author: wow

customer_reviews.title: My cat loves everything... except the tuna in this variety pack :-(
customer_reviews.text: My cat eats absolutely everything, but WILL NOT TOUCH the tuna selection here. We buy her the cheapest fancy feast garbage all the way up to grain free hand selected tuna loins, and even our own shellfish (from our dinner table). She will not touch this Tuna. The other two flavors she loves, but it is simply not cost effective to only use 2/3 of this variety pack. Reviews on Rachel Ray's site also agree, cats either love or hate this stuff. It is clearly real, quality fish and natural ingredients. I also like the containers are clear plastic, not cans (they resemble applesauce cups).
customer_reviews.author: j.b.cst

customer_reviews.title: Concerns with this cat food
customer_reviews.text: My 4 cats got sick on this food. Vomiting - so....... I thought perhaps my 4 kitties had a sensitive tummy. I'm a giving person so I gave to my friend to feed her kitties on October 16, 2018 - She told me last night her cats got sick and will not eat this food again. She said she'd meant to tell me earlier but had just slipped her mind. How might I be compensated or given credit for this purchase?
customer_reviews.author: BRENDA

customer_reviews.title: They added wierd spongy pieces!!
customer_reviews.text: I used to love this. Now theyve started adding these little squares that are like sponges that are really hard to smash and im afraid my cats will choke!! Plus it's more work for me to try to smash then. My cats leave all these squares in their bowls if I don't smash them so it's a total waste. And this is already really extensive food. Im so disappointed as this was the one food that seemed quality, not filler. Guess they are trying to cut corners!
customer_reviews.author: Kristen N

customer_reviews.title: SO FAR MY CATS LOVE IT!
customer_reviews.text: My cats are finicky eaters, so we have to keep changing and trying different brands of wet and dry food. I was worried to buy this because of the bad reviews. Thought my cats won’t eat it or if they eat they’ll loose they’re hair. So far, they love it. It’s grain free and made with real ingredients. You can see the shreds of chicken and fish (depending on the flavors). I don’t see any allergic reactions to my feline companions, so I recommend for you to try this for your furriends.
customer_reviews.author: Furriends Corner

customer_reviews.title: My cat didn't care for this
customer_reviews.text: Although I do like the dry food (so does my cat) the wet food she is very picky about...for some reason, even though it has a strong smell so I guess that means it's very fresh (?) my cat only eats the gravy part and will REFUSE to eat any of the chicken flavor one. My cat literally loves wet food so much I have NEVER in her 10 years had her refuse to even eat wet food before. I switched back to Purina and Fancy Feast and sure enough, she is fine and gobbles it up! Not sure about other cats, but if you're on the fence I wouldn't risk it.
customer_reviews.author: Dia-mond

customer_reviews.title: Feral cats hate this
customer_reviews.text: I bought this RR Nutrish wet food tuna for my 5 cat feral colony as a "break" from dry food. One cat took 2 licks, the others sniffed it and walked away. There were huge chunks of tuna in each container! Why don't these pet food manufacturers realize cats prefer small bits or pate? I had to cut up the food, and did notice bones as mentioned by another reviewer. Save your money; don't buy this. I should have known better since my ferals don't like RR Nutrish dry cat food, either.
customer_reviews.author: Marc1

customer_reviews.title: My cat has a digestive problem and this wet food ...
customer_reviews.text: My cat has a digestive problem and this wet food works well for him and he loves it. I was purchasing this food from Chewy but found out it is cheaper on Amazon and plus the shipping is free so that works for me.
customer_reviews.author: Shopping Diva

customer_reviews.title: No complaints. Cats love it.
customer_reviews.text: My two young cats love this stuff, and they can't wait for moist food time. Infact, I get a 4am wake up most days. I am a new pet owner, having only had cats as a kid. I recall that moist food tended to create an unpleasant litter box smell and mess, so I wasn't sure how often I wanted to feed moist food to my kittens. I have been feeding Nutrish once every day, and the cats can eat their dry food whenever they feel like it. Their bodies seem to be just find with the food.
customer_reviews.author: Bethany Mathews

customer_reviews.title: my cats lick the sauce off and leave the solids
customer_reviews.text: While my senior cat would eat this - and he was picky - he would lick the sauce off and leave the solids. I don't know what's in the solid bits, cubes and such, but even my other cats who will eat anything tend to leave it on the plate. I would love to buy just a small can of the sauce as a treat.
customer_reviews.author: Native Texan

customer_reviews.title: Cats' dream food!
customer_reviews.text: Our 9 year old cats go nuts for this stuff. They love it! They eat it up and it seems to be easy for them to digest. Since being on this tuna diet for about 6 mos, they tear around the house - as active as kittens. Less hair balls too? I will switch the food flavors up for them I suppose, now and them but this has been a winner here for happy and healthy cats.
customer_reviews.author: Jan

customer_reviews.title: Something wrong with this food
customer_reviews.text: Not sure why but my cats absolutely hated this food. I have two cats and am watching two cats temporarily. All four cats took initial bites and then made faces and acted like they were trying to get the food off their tongues. They seriously did not like it. Amazon refunded without requiring a return (thabk you) so I considered giving it away. After thinking about it, I was not comfortable doing that so threw the rest away...2+ boxes of food. Something was wrong with this food.
customer_reviews.author: RLS

customer_reviews.title: All three of my cats seriously disliked this.
customer_reviews.text: Other Nutrish foods have been ok, but this one seems to really displease all of my cats: one wouldn't touch it; another who generally eats hers and others' leftovers (if I let her) actually left it unfinished; the third vomited twice after eating a few bites. It also seems to have a lot of processed nuggets where as other Nutrish food had mostly/all identifiable chunks of the actual meat included. Three cats don't make for a strong sample size, sure, but it's definitely a pattern.
customer_reviews.author: Roger Austin

customer_reviews.title: CATS LOVE IT
customer_reviews.text: My picky eater kitten prefers this over patè cat food like IAMs and Sheba. I would suggest to put the opened or unopened packs in the fridge to make them stay fresh. I don’t want my cats to get salmonella. What I do is just prepare half for the kitten and heat it up in microwave for 10 seconds.
customer_reviews.author: Furriends Corner

customer_reviews.title: My cats won't even touch it
customer_reviews.text: The food actually looks like real food and I was really hopeful that my cats will finally want to eat something grain-free and healthy. Other grain-free cat food has been hit-and-miss, but this particular food they didn't want to even approach their plate closer than a foot away... whatever "nutrish" ingredients are in there dear Rachel, it's totally wasted if cats hate the smell/taste. What a waste of $$
customer_reviews.author: Vesna

customer_reviews.title: Great Find
customer_reviews.text: My cat is very old and has renal disease, so her food is pretty boring. I wanted a healthy treat that she could enjoy. I've read a lot of labels and compared prices. This is such a find! She is not tempted by most canned food, seemingly pate, so it will just sit out and get hard. As soon as this came, I opened one up. Once she smelled it, she inhaled it! That made me so happy. The food is moist in yummy sauce, but also with pieces. So gourmet! Thank you for such a great product :)
customer_reviews.author: Amazon Customer

customer_reviews.title: The best food ever!
customer_reviews.text: My 13 year old cat has never been so happy. I’ve been feeding him rachel rays chicken exclusively for about a month now. Prior to this no matter what food it was he would get sick, his coat would have candor and his eyes would get goopy. Obviously he had an allergy to something in every other brand on the shelf and even prescribed. I cannot recommend this more. By the way he is a purebred Persian.
customer_reviews.author: BPE

customer_reviews.title: Picky cat likes
customer_reviews.text: Steven is the pickiest cat I've ever had and this is his favorite. The protein-fat-carb ratio could be better, but he likes it so I'll keep buying it. I've tried switching him to the more expensive, but healthier Tiki Cat brand wet food, and he is not as enthused. This brand is good enough quality without breaking the bank.
customer_reviews.author: TipaTac

customer_reviews.title: BEST Cat food ever. Seeing is Believing!!
customer_reviews.text: Unbelievable!! It looks and smells good enough for me to grab a fork. If you LOVE your cat..try this. I did learn that for some reason Happy want me to mush up the small meat bits or she will leave them. But hey...we all have our own quirks. This is the very BEST cat food ever. I'm not even done with 1st box and she already knows the difference in her two foods.
customer_reviews.author: Ruth

customer_reviews.title: Pepper absolutely loves it!
customer_reviews.text: My cat pepper started to not want to eat her food, so I started mixing this into her kibble and she absolutely loves it! She actually tries to jump on my shoulders, sometimes successfully, in order to steal the small cup of cat food before I'm done opening it! I love the there are only ingredients that you can read and recognize in this cat food, my only complaint is that I wish the portion sizes were specific to the type of cat you have. The reason I say that is because my cat never finishes 1 Cup in a day.
customer_reviews.author: Marisa Navarro-Gonzalez

customer_reviews.title: My cats are finicky so this is a tough call
customer_reviews.text: My cats won't eat it. They don't like the gravy to processed food mouth feel, I'm guessing? I don't know. All I think of when I see it is those cooked Processed Banquet Dinners? Adult humans don't like it, so why would cats? I love her dry food and I've actually met her but yeah this isn't the best thought out product.
customer_reviews.author: corduroyspocket

customer_reviews.title: I love my cats so this is actually a quarter of ...
customer_reviews.text: I'm assuming it's up to the digestive tract of your cat butt my cats wouldn't eat it all and one of the cats regurgitated and vomited. I love my cats so this is actually a quarter of a star if I have the option. I threw the rest of the product away and I definitely cannot recommend it unless your cat has a metal digestive tract unable to swallow and eat just about anything
customer_reviews.author: C. Pierre

customer_reviews.title: Our cats seem to love this food and we appreciate the plastic containers that ...
customer_reviews.text: Our cats seem to love this food and we appreciate the plastic containers that don't require a can opener. We were buying Science Diet for years but new cat doesn't seem to eat it so we looked for an alternative. We started buying this Rachel Ray food in bulk on Amazon rather than from the local supermarket.
customer_reviews.author: Jimmy

customer_reviews.title: My Cat Loves It
customer_reviews.text: Wow I’m so shocked at how many people find bones in the food! That’s horrible! However, I haven’t found any bones in the food I got for my cat. I bought the 24 can one. My cat really loves it and she has not gotten sick. I give her one a day. She is very happy with it. I hope that Racheal Ray does fix the bone issue for all the products. Overall it looks healthy and fresh.
customer_reviews.author: Marina M.

customer_reviews.title: Good Variety and Good For Them.
customer_reviews.text: I wanted a wet food with the right nutritious ingredients specifically for cats and I wanted a variety. This was just the thing. The little plastic containers (about like an individual apple sauce size and type) are pressed full of veggies, meat, and a little broth. My cats aren't particularly picky. They tried it and were slow to finish it, but then licked it clean. They enjoy all three meat dishes.
customer_reviews.author: Sophia Rose

customer_reviews.title: My cats thought it was “meh.”
customer_reviews.text: I’m having to go by my cats’ response to the flavor since I definitely didn’t try it myself. They seem to like the chicken entrees better the fish entrees by Rachel Ray. The pieces of fish are too large for cat mouths. I end up having to mince the pieces so they eat more. Can I just tell you that cutting up cat food for my three cats is a bit much even for me?
customer_reviews.author: Bookshop Without Borders

customer_reviews.title: Kitty loves it and healthy
customer_reviews.text: I just got a kitten who stuck up her nose at any wet food I offered her... I was getting frantic thinking that she just had to eat something it became an obsession then I tried this wonderful food and SHE ATE IT !!!!!!! I could see a difference right away.. Now she can't wait to get her food and my biggest problem is watching her flying through the house like a crazy kitty not to mention all the money spent on all the other food rejects.
customer_reviews.author: myfavorites

customer_reviews.title: Our cat with a weak stomach loves it and that's saying a lot.
customer_reviews.text: One cat in particular has a bit of a weak stomach and when food doesn't agree with him and it won't stay down. When he doesn't like a particular brand of food he just won't eat so when he ate this and it stays down it's always a good sign. Out other cats are enjoying it, too so it's a win-win.
customer_reviews.author: The Shadow Knows

customer_reviews.title: Love the idea of the product for my kitties, they just didn't take to it.
customer_reviews.text: I wanted to let you know that unfortunately my kitties didn't take to this product. I was unhappy that they didn't because I liked the quality of the product, however they were used to square morsels with gravy from Max Cat/Nutro and I think it was a texture thing for them. I would love if you offered products with various forms of the cat food such as morsels. I want to let you know since you didn't ask for the product to be returned I gave it to a shelter kitty.
customer_reviews.author: kathleen kendall

customer_reviews.title: My cats like it but the kittens don’t
customer_reviews.text: My cats like it but the kittens don’t. Kind of funny the cats go crazy over it but my younger kittens don’t care for it probably it’s too wet for them I’m not sure why. It’s a little pricey package nice and on time. They really love their dry food and the kittens really like the dry food of hers Rachel
customer_reviews.author: CHB&charles

customer_reviews.title: Cat approved.... atleast for now
customer_reviews.text: My cat LOVES this! Usually I have to chase her around the house with her bowl to get her to finish her food. With this chicken lover pack, she cleans her plate on her own. No more chasing for me..... for now. Who knows, cats are picky and are known to change their mind in a nano second😼
customer_reviews.author: Susana

customer_reviews.title: Cats hated it
customer_reviews.text: I have two cats and three rescues that I saved this winter and am trying to find homes for. Only one of the cats touched the food and they love kitty wet food! I’m sad it was such a waste of money and didn’t appear to have any salmon just mostly chicken and peas. I was hoping for a healthy option so I paid more for nothing bc they won’t even try it! My cats finally tried this and then they all puked everywhere. I talked to my friend who tried it and she said it made her cats sick too. This food = Cat Vomit.
customer_reviews.author: Kathleen Coelho

customer_reviews.title: Found Bones.
customer_reviews.text: I've ordered this product three times and hadn't yet had this issue, but I finally found bones in a container of 'Ocean-Fish-a-Liscous'. I had to throw out the entire container and will likely be throwing out the rest of this flavor. I won't be reordering this product. And unless you want to spend the time going through each individual container with a fine tooth comb to see if there's bones, I wouldn't recommend it either. PS if you think this is a rare occurrence, scroll down a little further. This isn't an isolated incident.
customer_reviews.author: Alex

customer_reviews.title: FINICKY RAGDOLL LOVES NUTRISH WET CAT FOOD!
customer_reviews.text: Great shipping service - of course! The price is very affordable. As far as the Nutrish Wet Cat Food, well my kitty absolutely eats it up! What more could a cat mom say? He's happy and I'm happy. My cat is a Ragdoll, by the way, and he can be fairly finicky.
customer_reviews.author: MrsJ

customer_reviews.title: My cat would not eat it.
customer_reviews.text: Usually I feed my cat FANCY FEAST, which is significantly cheaper. I thought she would love this. Sadly, she wouldn't touch it. The only other food she refuses is food with grain or vegetables mixed in. Thought she would go for it as it is supposed to be all meat. Either she is very spoiled, or something is wrong with this cat food.
customer_reviews.author: peepers

customer_reviews.title: Well what can I say
customer_reviews.text: The cat won't eat it. They lick it dry and it just stays there. I even tried to leave it and remove all other foods thinking they would get hungry enough and it still didn't work. I bought the Chicken lovers it that makes a difference. 20 bucks wasted. The only reason for two stars is at least she like the liquid in it.
customer_reviews.author: Valhalla

customer_reviews.title: Simba got sick from it
customer_reviews.text: I’ve tried giving this foot to my cat, Simba. The first box I bought made him throw up every time I gave it to him. So I tried a different flavor. He sniffs it and then walks away. So I have all the cans just sitting in the box. I don’t want him throwing up or going without food bc he doesn’t like it. I had high hopes for this product but I wasted my money. I won’t be buying any more of this product again. Btw, the first can I have him made him puke...what concerned me was the reddish tint of his vomit. It looked like streaks of blood.
customer_reviews.author: A. Blenstroub

customer_reviews.title: Wanting to be sure my senior cat was getting enough ...
customer_reviews.text: Wanting to be sure my senior cat was getting enough hydration I decided to supplement her diet of dry food with a grain free wet option. She has never had an interest in people food and only a slight interest in canned food as a treat, however she immediately took to this food and now gets 1/2 to 1 tub a day as a supplement to a ~1/4 cup of kibbles.
customer_reviews.author: azblue

customer_reviews.title: Made for dumb humans, not cats.
customer_reviews.text: Kitties hate it and they are not typically picky. You can tell this was made to appeal to humans visually with no care as to the experience of the ones eating it. I have bought this brand dry cat food before and same results, this is the last time. Taking the remaining cups to the feral cat food bank.
customer_reviews.author: Kelly

customer_reviews.title: Catfood for Finicky Cats
customer_reviews.text: While searching for cat food for my finicky cats I discovered RR's wholesome food. Grain free, my cats quite enjoy the flavors. It can be hard to find in local stores near me. Amazon delivers everything my cats need. I also like the dry good, too. My kitties love it!
customer_reviews.author: Mary Eve

customer_reviews.title: Seems to have quality ingredients but cats wouldn't eat it
customer_reviews.text: I have 2 cats. 1 is way overweight because he will eat anything. He's a frickin goat. He would not eat this. Neither would the other. It's rare to find something neither will touch. The ingredients appear to be good quality but the cats just didn't approve.
customer_reviews.author: RJH85

customer_reviews.title: My Tom Loves Rachael Ray Tuna Purrfection
customer_reviews.text: I used to give my Tom another brand, until he got deathly ill from a serving. I purchased a Rachael Ray variety pack, so he could do some taste testing. He loves Tuna Purrfection and has never gotten ill from this product. He's been enjoying Tuna Purrfection for about 2 1/2 years now, I highly recommend your pet try taste testing of Rachael Ray products, until you find the one your baby likes.
customer_reviews.author: FatBoy

customer_reviews.title: The smells good & looks good!
customer_reviews.text: The smells good looks good looks like homemade cooking But my cats didn't really like it. They will eat some but not all.😭. Is good on their belly though they don't vomit after eating it like they do some other food. That's why I tried this. The dry food does well on their stomachs too
customer_reviews.author: empressofq

customer_reviews.title: The Chicken and Shrimp Food cats smells like formaldehyde !
customer_reviews.text: I have tried the Tuna Perfection and Fish-o-Licious food with some success but the Chicken and Fish has an awful odor and my four cats will not touch it. I looked at the expiration date and for signs of poor packaging and it appeared to be in good condition. It smells like formaldehyde or some kind of plastic. Not sure why but there are many other products that I can use. I won't be purchasing this in the future.
customer_reviews.author: Dennis W75

customer_reviews.title: Looked and smelled good
customer_reviews.text: Smelled good, looked good, cats wouldn't eat it for some reason. Many cats are finicky so I can not rate the product as bad. So it is average in my opinion, it looked and smelled like most other wet cat foods i have tried. Give it a try see if your cat likes it!
customer_reviews.author: G. Fox

customer_reviews.title: my cats won't eat it
customer_reviews.text: I was impressed that these smelled like chicken people would eat...however, none of my cats, nor any of my son's cats would eat it. That is nine cats of assorted sizes, breeds, and ages that would not at this food. On the other hand, when I put it outside for the night, a cat, possum, or other visitor did eat it.
customer_reviews.author: Celia J. Powles

customer_reviews.title: Your can we all just love you so behind us for them!
customer_reviews.text: Gave to my neighbor whose cat just gobbled it up. My cat Bella, it’s over 10 years old and she only eats creamy things. You can tell the ingredients or first grade it’s just that my girl is too old and she eats baby tape formulas. Have no fear your cat will love it💕
customer_reviews.author: Haven’t read it Just put in in it in my did not want to miss it. library

customer_reviews.title: Nice package
customer_reviews.text: Overall I like the packaging, size, convenience of delivery, and the texture of the food, but my cats do not like it. I don't know whats wrong with this chicken dish from RR because it looks like it would e tasty, but my kitties, and those cats of my family-members with whom I have shared, do not like it. maybe I just received a bad case of food, but they don't like it so i can't buy it again.
customer_reviews.author: Jane Thompson

customer_reviews.title: My cats love, love
customer_reviews.text: My cats love, love, love it and it is grain free for them. Not the cheapest nor the more expensive cat food. Really convenient single servings, so much easier to deal with than cans. And, I recycle the little plastic bowl. Ships well and will continue to buy it.
customer_reviews.author: Jan

customer_reviews.title: Stopped feeding it to my cats
customer_reviews.text: I had to stop serving this food completely when the feral cat I feed refused to eat any of it past a couple of bites. My domestic cats ate around the “pellets” of flavored food in each can / plastic container of this cat food. Ultimately removed from my Amazon Subscribe and Save subscription. Something wasnt right any more about the product.
customer_reviews.author: E.  Wharton

customer_reviews.title: My Cats Love It
customer_reviews.text: My cats have to be on a protein diet to avoid health issues. I wasn’t certain they would like this good after reading the reviews. But all 3 gave a 5 paws up! They love it!! My only complaint is the size of the containers.
customer_reviews.author: tarotsirena

product_meta.title: Rachael Ray Nutrish Wet Cat Food, 2.8 Ounce Cups, Grain Free
product_meta.description: Flavor Name:Variety Pack - Ocean Lovers| Size:(12) 2.8 Oz. CupsPoultry by-product meal? Artificial flavors? Preservatives? No thanks! At Rachael Ray Nutrish, all of our recipes are prepared highest quality products—that's why you'll find real chicken or fish is the first ingredient in each of the selections in this appetizing variety pack. With a variety that includes Ocean Fish-a-Licious with chunks of ocean fish and tuna, Chicken & Shrimp Pawttenesca and Tuna Purrrfection, your cat's meals will never be boring or bland. A savory sauce adds flavor that takes this wet cat food from good to pawtastic! The seafood in this natural wet cat food provides a great source of omega fatty acids to support your healthy skin and a shiny coat. Plus, a portion of the proceeds from the sale of this product will be donated to the Rachael Ray Foundation, which helps pets in need through Rachael's Rescue, so you can feel good about serving a nutritious meal that will also benefit his feline friends across the country!
feature_bullets: Contains (12) 2.8 Ounce Cups of Wet Cat Food (4 Ocean Fish-A-Licious, 4 Chicken & Shrimp Pawttenesca, 4 Tuna Purrfection)
Real fish or chicken is the #1 ingredient in each delicious recipe
No meat by-products or filler ingredients
Grain-free recipe with no artificial flavors, colors or artificial preservatives
Natural wet cat food with added vitamins, minerals & taurine
